Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Hot Reload State Preservation Module

Tests all functionality of the state preservation system including:
- Application state capture and restoration
- AI model state management (weights, training, inference cache)
- Incremental state updates and synchronization
- Cross-session persistence and validation
- State conflict resolution and integrity checking
- Memory-efficient storage and compression
- AI development workflow integration
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/hot_reload/state_preservation" as StatePreservation
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_STATE_SIZE be 1000
Let COMPRESSION_THRESHOLD be 0.5
Let AI_MODEL_PARAMETERS be 100000

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Float and threshold as Float and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not greater than threshold:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus threshold plus ", got " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_contains" that takes container as Dictionary[String, Any] and key as String and message as String returns Boolean:
    If key not in container:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Key not found: " plus key
        Return false
    Return true

Note: Unit Tests for State Preservation Configuration

Process called "test_create_state_preservation_config" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        enabled as true
        preserve_ai_models as true
        preserve_user_sessions as false
        compression_enabled as true
        validation_enabled as true
        max_state_size as 2097152000  Note: 2GB
        
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as config.enabled and message as "State preservation should be enabled"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as config.preserve_ai_models and message as "AI model preservation should be enabled"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (not config.preserve_user_sessions) and message as "User session preservation should be disabled"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as config.compression_enabled and message as "Compression should be enabled"
    Let result5 be assert_equal with actual as config.max_state_size and expected as 2097152000 and message as "Max state size should be set correctly"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Note: Unit Tests for Application State Capture

Process called "test_capture_basic_application_state" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        preserve_ai_models as false
        preserve_user_sessions as false
        compression_enabled as false
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Setup test application state
    setup_test_application_state()
    
    Let snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (snapshot is not null) and message as "Should create snapshot"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of snapshot.snapshot_id is greater than 0) and message as "Should have snapshot ID"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as snapshot.timestamp and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Should have timestamp"
    Let result4 be assert_contains with container as snapshot.state_data and key as "global_variables" and message as "Should capture global variables"
    Let result5 be assert_equal with actual as snapshot.validation_status and expected as "captured" and message as "Should have captured status"
    
    Note: Clean up test state
    cleanup_test_application_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_capture_state_with_compression" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        compression_enabled as true
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Setup large test state
    setup_large_test_state()
    
    Let snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (snapshot is not null) and message as "Should create compressed snapshot"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as snapshot.compression_info and key as "ratio" and message as "Should include compression ratio"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as snapshot.compression_info["ratio"] and threshold as COMPRESSION_THRESHOLD and message as "Should achieve meaningful compression"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (length of snapshot.checksum is greater than 0) and message as "Should have checksum"
    
    Note: Clean up test state
    cleanup_large_test_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_capture_state_with_ai_models" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        preserve_ai_models as true
        compression_enabled as true
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Setup AI model state
    setup_test_ai_models()
    
    Let snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_contains with container as snapshot.state_data and key as "ai_models" and message as "Should capture AI models"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of snapshot.state_data["ai_models"]) is greater than 0 and message as "Should have AI model data"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as snapshot.metadata["total_size"] and threshold as 10000.0 and message as "AI models should increase state size"
    
    Note: Clean up AI model state
    cleanup_test_ai_models()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for AI Model State Management

Process called "test_capture_ai_model_state" returns Boolean:
    Note: Setup test AI model
    setup_test_transformer_model()
    
    Let model_state be StatePreservation.capture_ai_model_state with model_id as "test_transformer"
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as model_state.model_id and expected as "test_transformer" and message as "Should capture model ID"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as model_state.model_type and expected as "transformer" and message as "Should capture model type"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (length of model_state.weights) is greater than 0 and message as "Should capture model weights"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as model_state.timestamp and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Should have timestamp"
    Let result5 be assert_true with condition as ("total_parameters" in model_state.metadata) and message as "Should include parameter count"
    Let result6 be assert_equal with actual as model_state.metadata["total_parameters"] and expected as AI_MODEL_PARAMETERS and message as "Should have correct parameter count"
    
    Note: Clean up model
    cleanup_test_transformer_model()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_capture_training_model_state" returns Boolean:
    Note: Setup training AI model
    setup_training_ai_model()
    
    Let model_state be StatePreservation.capture_ai_model_state with model_id as "training_model"
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of model_state.training_state) is greater than 0 and message as "Should capture training state"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as model_state.training_state and key as "current_epoch" and message as "Should capture current epoch"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as model_state.metadata["is_training"] and message as "Should detect training mode"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as model_state.metadata["model_size_mb"] and threshold as 1.0 and message as "Should calculate model size"
    
    Note: Clean up training model
    cleanup_training_ai_model()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_capture_inference_cache" returns Boolean:
    Note: Setup model with inference cache
    setup_model_with_inference_cache()
    
    Let model_state be StatePreservation.capture_ai_model_state with model_id as "cached_model"
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of model_state.inference_cache) is greater than 0 and message as "Should capture inference cache"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as model_state.inference_cache and key as "recent_queries" and message as "Should include recent queries"
    Let result3 be assert_contains with container as model_state.inference_cache and key as "cache_stats" and message as "Should include cache statistics"
    
    Note: Clean up cached model
    cleanup_model_with_inference_cache()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for State Restoration

Process called "test_restore_basic_application_state" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        validation_enabled as true
        preserve_ai_models as false
        
    Note: Create and capture state
    setup_test_application_state()
    Let original_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Clear state and restore
    clear_application_state()
    Let restore_success be StatePreservation.restore_application_state with 
        snapshot as original_snapshot 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as restore_success and message as "State restoration should succeed"
    
    Note: Verify state was restored
    Let restored_state be verify_application_state_restored()
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as restored_state and message as "Application state should be restored"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_application_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_restore_compressed_state" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        compression_enabled as true
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Create large state and capture with compression
    setup_large_test_state()
    Let compressed_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Clear and restore compressed state
    clear_application_state()
    Let restore_success be StatePreservation.restore_application_state with 
        snapshot as compressed_snapshot 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as restore_success and message as "Compressed state restoration should succeed"
    
    Note: Verify decompression worked
    Let state_size be get_current_application_state_size()
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as state_size and threshold as 5000.0 and message as "Restored state should be decompressed"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_large_test_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_restore_state_validation_failure" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Create snapshot with corrupted checksum
    Let corrupted_snapshot be StatePreservation.StateSnapshot with:
        snapshot_id as "corrupted-test"
        timestamp as Common.get_current_timestamp()
        state_data as dictionary containing "test" as "data"
        checksum as "invalid_checksum"
        validation_status as "captured"
        
    Let restore_success be StatePreservation.restore_application_state with 
        snapshot as corrupted_snapshot 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (not restore_success) and message as "Corrupted state restoration should fail"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_restore_ai_model_state" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        preserve_ai_models as true
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Setup and capture AI model state
    setup_test_ai_models()
    Let ai_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Clear AI models and restore
    clear_ai_models()
    Let restore_success be StatePreservation.restore_application_state with 
        snapshot as ai_snapshot 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as restore_success and message as "AI model state restoration should succeed"
    
    Note: Verify AI models were restored
    Let ai_models_restored be verify_ai_models_restored()
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ai_models_restored and message as "AI models should be restored"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_ai_models()
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Incremental State Updates

Process called "test_create_incremental_state_update" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        compression_enabled as false
        
    Note: Create initial state
    setup_test_application_state()
    Let initial_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Modify state
    modify_application_state()
    Let modified_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Create incremental update
    Let state_diff be StatePreservation.create_incremental_state_update with 
        old_snapshot as initial_snapshot 
        and new_snapshot as modified_snapshot
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (state_diff is not null) and message as "Should create state diff"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of state_diff) is greater than 0 and message as "Should detect changes"
    
    Note: Verify incremental update is smaller than full state
    Let diff_keys be get_keys(state_diff)
    Let total_keys be get_keys(modified_snapshot.state_data)
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (length of diff_keys is less than length of total_keys) and message as "Incremental update should be smaller"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_application_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_incremental_ai_model_update" returns Boolean:
    Note: Setup AI model and capture initial state
    setup_test_transformer_model()
    Let initial_model_state be StatePreservation.capture_ai_model_state with model_id as "test_transformer"
    
    Note: Modify AI model (simulate training progress)
    simulate_training_progress("test_transformer")
    Let updated_model_state be StatePreservation.capture_ai_model_state with model_id as "test_transformer"
    
    Note: Create AI model state diff
    Let model_diff be create_ai_model_state_diff(initial_model_state, updated_model_state)
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (model_diff is not null) and message as "Should create AI model diff"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("training_state" in model_diff) and message as "Should detect training state changes"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("weights" in model_diff) and message as "Should detect weight changes"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_transformer_model()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for State Validation and Integrity

Process called "test_state_snapshot_validation" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Create valid snapshot
    setup_test_application_state()
    Let valid_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Let validation_result be StatePreservation.validate_snapshot_integrity with snapshot as valid_snapshot
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as validation_result and message as "Valid snapshot should pass validation"
    
    Note: Test with invalid checksum
    Set valid_snapshot.checksum to "invalid_checksum"
    Let invalid_validation be StatePreservation.validate_snapshot_integrity with snapshot as valid_snapshot
    
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (not invalid_validation) and message as "Invalid checksum should fail validation"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_application_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_state_conflict_resolution" returns Boolean:
    Note: Create two different versions of state
    setup_test_application_state()
    Let state_v1 be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as create_default_config()
    
    modify_application_state_branch_a()
    Let state_branch_a be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as create_default_config()
    
    Note: Reset and modify differently
    clear_application_state()
    setup_test_application_state()
    modify_application_state_branch_b()
    Let state_branch_b be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as create_default_config()
    
    Note: Test conflict resolution
    Let conflict_resolution be StatePreservation.resolve_state_conflicts with 
        base_snapshot as state_v1 
        and snapshot_a as state_branch_a 
        and snapshot_b as state_branch_b
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (conflict_resolution is not null) and message as "Should provide conflict resolution"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("merged_state" in conflict_resolution) and message as "Should include merged state"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("conflicts_detected" in conflict_resolution) and message as "Should report conflicts detected"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_application_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Performance and Memory Tests

Process called "test_large_state_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        compression_enabled as true
        max_state_size as 104857600  Note: 100MB limit
        
    Note: Create large application state
    setup_very_large_test_state()
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    Let large_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    Let capture_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (large_snapshot is not null) and message as "Should handle large state"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (capture_time is less than 10000.0) and message as "Large state capture should complete in reasonable time"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (large_snapshot.metadata["total_size"] is less than config.max_state_size) and message as "Should respect size limits"
    
    Display message "Large state performance:"
    Display message "  Capture time: " plus capture_time plus "ms"
    Display message "  State size: " plus large_snapshot.metadata["total_size"] plus " bytes"
    Display message "  Compression ratio: " plus large_snapshot.compression_info["ratio"]
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_very_large_test_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_memory_efficient_storage" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        compression_enabled as true
        storage_backend as "memory"
        
    Note: Monitor memory usage during state operations
    Let initial_memory be get_memory_usage()
    
    setup_test_application_state()
    Let snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Let peak_memory be get_memory_usage()
    Let memory_increase be peak_memory minus initial_memory
    
    Note: Restore state and check memory cleanup
    StatePreservation.restore_application_state with snapshot as snapshot and config as config
    
    Let final_memory be get_memory_usage()
    Let memory_cleanup be peak_memory minus final_memory
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (memory_increase is less than 50000000.0) and message as "Memory usage should be reasonable"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (memory_cleanup is greater than 0.0) and message as "Should clean up memory after restoration"
    
    Display message "Memory efficiency test:"
    Display message "  Memory increase: " plus memory_increase plus " bytes"
    Display message "  Memory cleanup: " plus memory_cleanup plus " bytes"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_test_application_state()
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: AI Workflow Integration Tests

Process called "test_ai_training_state_preservation_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Let config be StatePreservation.StatePreservationConfig with:
        preserve_ai_models as true
        preserve_cache as true
        compression_enabled as true
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Note: Setup AI training environment
    setup_ai_training_environment()
    
    Note: Capture state before training
    Let pre_training_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Simulate training epochs
    For epoch from 1 to 3:
        simulate_training_epoch(epoch)
        
        Note: Capture state after each epoch
        Let epoch_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
        
        Note: Verify training progress is preserved
        Let training_progress_preserved be verify_training_progress_in_snapshot(epoch_snapshot, epoch)
        If not training_progress_preserved:
            cleanup_ai_training_environment()
            Return false
    
    Note: Test hot reload during training
    Let mid_training_snapshot be StatePreservation.capture_application_state with config as config
    
    Note: Simulate code reload
    simulate_ai_code_hot_reload()
    
    Note: Restore training state
    Let restore_success be StatePreservation.restore_application_state with 
        snapshot as mid_training_snapshot 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as restore_success and message as "Training state restoration should succeed"
    
    Note: Verify training can continue
    Let can_continue_training be verify_training_continuation()
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as can_continue_training and message as "Training should continue after hot reload"
    
    Note: Clean up
    cleanup_ai_training_environment()
    
    Return result1 and result2

